records.addlTxt: Notice of bond forfeiture mailed to defendant. ($1,000.00 signature bond) LW

Defendant Selena Shanice Cole not in court.  Stephanie Krueger appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for calendar call.  Defendant does not appear.  Bench warrant was previously issued.  Court takes no further action at this time.
Signature bond ordered to be forfeited in the amount of 1000.00.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE JUDGE ON RETURN OF THE BENCH WARRANT.

Defendant Selena Shanice Cole not in court.  Samantha Raygo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a preliminary hearing 4/13/2022. The defendant having failed to appear, the court ordered a bench warrant to issue, any bond forfeited and Judgment of Bond Forfeiture 30 days after notification by the Clerk of Circuit Court.
Calendar call on May 3, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Selena Shanice Cole not in court.  Patrick O'Keefe appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for status conference.  Defendant does not have an attorney appointed.   Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a bench warrant issued but stayed the issuance until the next court date.  Case adjourned to Branch 40.  Calendar call scheduled for May 3, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Selena Shanice Cole not in court. Case was called on the record for adjournment due to no appointment of counsel. Clerk error regarding the appearance of the defendant. Clerk to address matters with Commissioner on 4/14/22.  Status conference scheduled for April 14, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Court ordered Justice Point Pretrial Services LEVEL 1 SUPERVISION.  Court reminders.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.
No Contact Order signed and filed.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Walmart at 401 E Capitol Dr, Milwaukee, Christopher Ottaway, except as necessary as Officer Ottaway perform his official duties as a police officer

Defendant Selena Shanice Cole in court with attorney Melissa Nepomiachi.  Defendant Selena Shanice Cole in custody.  Samantha Raygo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Selena Shanice Cole appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Shelton, Branch 40. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and dnenied.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Commissioner advised DNA sample has NOT been obtained from the Defendant.  Court ordered the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department to obtain DNA sample from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).  Preliminary hearing scheduled for April 13, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
